Considerations for Data Cloud Reports on Calculated Insights

Keep these considerations in mind when working with Data Cloud reports on calculated insights.

Calculated Insights Reports

Measures are treated as aggregates and dimensions are treated as groupings, and they aren’t interchangeable. All possible aggregates (measures) and groupings (dimensions) are added to reports by default.
A Calculated Insights report must have at least one aggregate measure and one grouping. You can’t create reports on calculated insight that don’t have measures or dimensions.
To include non-aggregatable measures in a report, first include all the dimensions from the calculated insight.
A calculated insight report displays as a summary report without details.
A calculated insight report doesn’t show grand totals and row count.
You can’t add row-level and summary formulas to a column.
You can’t perform aggregates, such as sum, min, max, and average on a measure.
Non-aggregatable measures in a report don’t show subtotals.
To build a report on calculated insights with more than five dimensions, include at least one aggregatable measure in the report.
For calculated insights with more than five dimensions and both aggregatable and non-aggregatable measures, you can build reports with up to five dimensions and all aggregatable measures. To add a dimension when five dimensions are present, delete an existing dimension from the report.
You can’t remove a grouping from a report with only non-aggregatable measures.
When you remove a dimension from the report, all non-aggregatable measures are also removed. When you add a dimension back to the report, you must add the measures you want.
You can’t export a calculated insight report using the Details Only option.

Charts in Calculated Insights Reports

Keep these considerations in mind when adding charts to a Calculated Insights report.

When you remove a dimension or measure from the report that is included in its chart, the chart refreshes to display valid data if possible. Otherwise, the report doesn’t display the chart anymore and you can’t add another chart to the report.
You can’t add non-aggregatable measures to the report’s chart until you add all the dimensions to the chart.

Calculated Insights Reports in Dashboards

All Calculated Insight report and chart behavior applies to the dashboard components using them.
Tabular, metric, and gauge components aren’t available.
title: Considerations for Data Cloud Reports on Calculated Insights
